<section class="section">

<h2>
From Molecular Clues to <span>Human Impact</span>
</h2>

<p>
Omics sciences do not replace clinical judgment, diagnosis, or medical care. Their value is in helping researchers understand biological mechanisms, discover biomarkers, classify disease more precisely, and develop better questions for future medicine.
</p>

<p>
For cancer, this means studying how molecular signals emerge, how tumors evolve, how the immune system responds, and why different people may experience different disease trajectories or treatment responses.
</p>

